"/> $150,000 per work is the maximum statutory damages. To reach that, the
plaintiff has to show that the infringement was willful, and the court
has to feel that that amount is reasonable and just. (The minimum if
the infringement is innocent is $200 per work, which can still be a lot
of money if somebody is &quot;sharing&quot; a thousand songs.)

