"/> Note that making an archive copy of a computer program is covered by
a specific section of the copyright statutes (17 USC 117) and is
limited to the &quot;owner&quot; of the particular copy. Some have said that
it does not cover &quot;licensees&quot; and there is reason to believe that
is the case. It covers only computer programs and not computer
data in general.

Any right to make an archive copy of other than a computer program
would come from a &quot;fair use&quot; argument or, in the case of musical
recordings, for the Audio Home Recording Act (17 USC 1001 et seq)
if the proper device or media is used.

